1)  DETAILED ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET IMAGE

•  Overall there are two separate “mini‐structures.”  
   –  Left Structure (“Table‐Like”):
      –  Four vertical orange cylinders form the legs.  
      –  Two flat green rectangular blocks lie side by side on top, creating a “table” surface.  
      –  This results in two layers:  
         •  Layer 1 (bottom): four upright orange cylinders.  
         •  Layer 2 (top): two horizontal green rectangular prisms.  

   –  Right Structure (“T‐Shaped”):
      –  A yellow half‐cylinder on the floor acts as the base.  
      –  A tall, vertical green rectangular block stands on top of the yellow half‐cylinder.  
      –  A horizontal orange cylinder rests across the top of the green block, forming a “T.”  
      –  This structure has three layers:  
         •  Layer 1 (bottom): one yellow half‐cylinder.  
         •  Layer 2 (middle): one vertical green block.  
         •  Layer 3 (top): one orange cylinder oriented horizontally.  

•  Total Block Count: 9 blocks in all (left structure uses 6, right structure uses 3).  

2)  SELECTING THE REQUIRED DICTIONARY BLOCKS

Matching each piece to the dictionary without rotating them differently than shown:

•  Left Structure (“Table‐Like”):  
   –  4 × Orange Cylinder Upright → Dictionary index 6 (repeated four times).  
   –  2 × Green Rectangular Block, Flat/Horizontal → Dictionary index 1 (repeated twice).  

•  Right Structure (“T‐Shaped”):  
   –  1 × Yellow Half‐Cylinder (vertical axis, curved side facing us) → Dictionary index 11.  
   –  1 × Green Block Tall/Vertical → Dictionary index 3.  
   –  1 × Orange Cylinder Horizontal → Dictionary index 8.  

Hence the needed indices are:  
[6, 6, 6, 6, 1, 1, 11, 3, 8]  

3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER 

{
  Step1: Move block with index 6    // first orange cylinder leg
  Step2: Move block with index 6    // second orange cylinder leg
  Step3: Move block with index 6    // third orange cylinder leg
  Step4: Move block with index 6    // fourth orange cylinder leg
  Step5: Move block with index 1    // first green top piece
  Step6: Move block with index 1    // second green top piece
  Step7: Move block with index 11   // yellow half‐cyl base
  Step8: Move block with index 3    // tall green block
  Step9: Move block with index 8    // horizontal orange cylinder
}
